            <h2>About Me</h2>
            <p>Hi! My name is Karina. I am a 22-year-old Mexican American woman. I love playing the trumpet and have a deep passion for mariachi music. Mariachi music is more than just a genre to me; it's a beautiful expression of Mexican culture and heritage.</p>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>The Beauty of Mariachi</h2>
            <p>Mariachi music has a rich history that dates back to the 18th century in Western Mexico. It is a blend of indigenous, African, and Spanish musical traditions. The lively music is often accompanied by dancing, and it plays a significant role in Mexican celebrations, from weddings to community gatherings.</p>
            <p>Mariachi music is characterized by its use of string instruments like the violin, vihuela, guitar, and guitarrón, and often includes trumpets and vocals. It's a symbol of Mexican pride and a way for many Mexican Americans to stay connected to their roots.</p>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>Reconnect with Your Heritage</h2>
            <p>If you are a young Mexican American, I encourage you to explore mariachi music. It’s a wonderful way to reconnect with your heritage and celebrate your culture. Playing mariachi music can be a source of joy, pride, and connection to your history.</p>
        </section>

